  m_Name: Forepaw_Digit3_Proximal_R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Forepaw_Digit3_Proximal_R
  partName: Forepaw Digit3 Proximal Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - "The right forepaw digit three proximal phalanx is the first phalangeal bone
    of the third digit within the canine forepaw. It connects the metacarpal bone
    to the middle phalanx, forming part of the digit\u2019s flexible joint system.This
    bone contributes to toe movement, balance, and efficient"
  - ' weight distribution during locomotion and standing activities. Tendons and
    ligaments attached to the proximal phalanx control flexion, extension, and stabilization
    of the digit. The third digit plays a significant role in supporting body weight
    and maintaining traction during movement.'
